      • mul

        public static MDD mul​(MDD mdd,
                      java.math.BigInteger m_min,
                      java.math.BigInteger m_max,
                      int n,
                      Domains D)
        This method return a MDD which respect the multiplicative constraint
        The multiplicative constraint ensure that if we multiply all the variables together, the result belong to the interval [m_min, m_max]. This method only works for positives numbers. As the product can be very hugh, the type of m_min and m_max is BigInteger
        Parameters:
        mdd - The MDD that will stock the result of the operation
        m_min - The lower bound of the constraint.
        m_max - The upper bound of the constraint.
        n - The number of variables.
        D - The domains of the variables.
        Returns:
        The MDD satisfying the multiplicative constraint.
